'''Michael Chu''' was a member of the [[Obsidian Entertainment]]'s Design Team on the [[2005]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''.<ref name="Game">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref> He is responsible for the writing of two companions : [[Bao-Dur]] and [[Canderous Ordo|Mandalore the Preserver]].<ref name="15 Years">{{WebCite|url=http://www.cinelinx.com/news/culture/knights-of-the-old-republic-ii-developer-chris-avellone-discusses-the-games-impact-15-years-later|text=Knights of the Old Republic II Developer Chris Avellone Discusses the Game's Impact 15 Years Later|author=Maison, Jordan|date=2019-12-06|work=[http://www.cinelinx.com Cinelinx]|quote=I had to write almost all the companions, except for Mandalore and Bao-Dur (who was written by Michael Chu[) &hellip;]|archivedate=20191208220416}}</ref>

